## Conventions for new skills

1. **Directory name = `name` field.** Lowercase, hyphens only.
2. **Body content stays public-safe.** No `mcp__cekura__*` tool refs, no internal endpoints, no MCP-server architecture details. Operational MCP details live in command files only.
3. **Stay under ~400 lines.** Move detail to `references/` and link.
4. **Public API endpoint paths are fine** (e.g., `POST /test_framework/v1/...`).
5. **Public provider names are fine** (VAPI, Retell, ElevenLabs, LiveKit, Pipecat, SIP) — they're documented at https://docs.cekura.ai/documentation/integrations/.
6. **Include the "Performing Platform Actions" directive verbatim** so Claude Code users get tool-preferred routing.
7. **Add an `agents/openai.yaml`** for nicer Codex UI (optional, ignored elsewhere).
8. **Bump `package.json` version** when adding/removing skills.
9. **Update README and CLAUDE.md** Quick Reference tables.
